The paper discusses the challenge of balancing data utility with privacy concerns in AI intensive systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed tool, PUT Workbench, involves data analysis and decision-making, which could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a privacy model, which could be related to cryptography (cs.CY).
